{"lemma":"صَباً","slug":"صَباً","root":"ص.ب.ب","root_slug":"ص-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَب","root":"صبب","pos":"V","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23626","n23737","n23742","n23743"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%8B"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pour out, to shed","examples":[{"text":"مَنِ ٱسْتَمَعَ إِلَى حَدِيثِ قَوْمٍ وَهُمْ لَهُ كَارِهُونَ أَوْ يَفِرُّونَ مِنْهُ، صُبَّ فِي أُذُنِهِ الآنُكُ يَوْمَ الْقِيَامَةِ.","english":"If somebody eavesdrops on a conversation of a party who disapproves or flees this molten lead will be poured into his ears on the Day of Resurrection."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be poured out, to flow","examples":[{"text":"يَصُبُّ نَهْرُ ٱلنِّيلِ فِي ٱلْبَحْرِ ٱلْأَبْيَضِ ٱلْمُتَوَسِّطِ","english":"The river Nile flows into the Mediterranean Sea."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to descend, to trickle down"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to embogue, to flow into, to undergo discharge into","examples":[{"text":"وأشار إلى أنه \"لايستبعد معارضة بعض الأطراف الكردية لهذا المشروع، لأنها تريد إبقاء لقمة عيش الناس بيدها وتستثمرها للابتزاز وكسب الولاء تبعا لمصالحها الحزبية\"، مستبعدا، \"الحل العاجل للأزمة بين بغداد وأربيل، ذلك أن حكومتي بغداد والإقليم غير جادتين في إيجاد حلول للأزمة، فبغداد تبحث عن مختلف الذرائع لكسر إرادة الإقليم، وتعتقد حكومة الإقليم أن حل الأزمة يضرّ بمصالحها الحزبية الضيقة وتريد لها أن تطول لأبعد وقت، لأنها تعتقد أن ذلك يصب في مصلحتها\".","english":"And he [زانا سعيد (Zānā Saʿīd), deputee of the Kurdistan Islamic Group] pointed out that “opposition of a part of the Kurdish parties for this bill is not excluded, because they want to keep the livelihood of the people in their hand, and exploit it for plundering and gaining loyality to their party interests”, excluding ”the needful solution for the crisis between Baġdād and ʾArbīl, this because the two governments of Baġdād and ʾArbīl aren’t big-hearted in finding solutions for the crisis, and Baġdād is seeking various pretexts for crushing the will of the region, and the territorial government believes that a solution of the crisis damages the narrow party interests and wants for it that it peruses a longer lapse of time, because it believes that this slots into their interest.”"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be affected by desire, to love heavily and suddenly"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"remnant, portion, residue in a vessel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَبَّ (ṣabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23626","headword_ar":"صَبَاَ","root":"SbA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuwo'N","text_ar":"صُبُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K, [in the last of which it is implied that this verb in all its senses except the last has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabo'N","text_ar":"صَبْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also for an inf. n., and likewise"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabuw^a","text_ar":"صَبُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a syn. form, but this I do not find authorized by any other lexicon,]) said of the tush (S, M, K) of a camel (S, M) and of a cloven-hoofed animal and of a solid-hoofed animal, (M,) and said of a cloven hoof, (K, [but this, I doubt not, is a mistake, for in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a AlZ~ilofu wAln~aAbu","text_ar":"صَبَاَ الظِّلْفُ والنَّابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reading in the K, I find in the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a naAbu AlZ~ilofi","text_ar":"صَبَاَ نَابُ الظِّلْفِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlxuf~i waAlHaAfiri","text_ar":"وَالخُفِّ وَالحَافِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like in the L,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It grew forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity, grew forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and accord. to the K, it appears that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASbA^","text_ar":"اصبا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; but this is not the case. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^at","text_ar":"صَبَاَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaniy~ap","text_ar":"ثَنِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. a central incisor] of a boy,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It grew forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  Also, said of a star, (M, K,) and of the moon, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It rose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASbA^","text_ar":"اصبا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSobaA^a Aln~ujuwmu","text_ar":"تَصْبَاَ النُّجُومُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars come forth from their places of rising:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^ati Aln~ujuwmu","text_ar":"صَبَاَتِ النُّجُومُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars appeared:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ajomu","text_ar":"النَّجْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASbA^","text_ar":"اصبا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Pleiades"},{"kind":"text","text":"[antonomastically called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alnjm","text_ar":"النجم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a","text_ar":"صَبَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a mino diynihi A_ilaY diynK A=xara","text_ar":"صَبَاَ مِنْ دِينِهِ اـِلَى دِينٍ ا=خَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AO, S, Msb, *) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuwo'N","text_ar":"صُبُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabo'N","text_ar":"صَبْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabuw^a","text_ar":"صَبُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuwo'apN","text_ar":"صُبُوْءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (CK [but not in the TA nor in my MS. copy of the K];) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He departed from his religion to another religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) like as the stars come forth from their place of rising. (AO, S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a","text_ar":"صَبَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a fiY diynihi","text_ar":"صَبَاَ فِى دِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuwo'N","text_ar":"صُبُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAbiy^","text_ar":"صَابِي"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sabian"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, S, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAbiy^N","text_ar":"صَابِيٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a Ealayohimo","text_ar":"صَبَاَ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabo'N","text_ar":"صَبْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuwo'N","text_ar":"صُبُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came forth upon them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASbA^","text_ar":"اصبا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a Ealayohi","text_ar":"صَبَاَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he came forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went forth, upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he inclined against him with enmity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he came,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came forth, upon him unexpectedly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, he says, the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sub~FA","text_ar":"صُبًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the saying of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lataEuwduwn~a fiyhaA A^asaAwida Sub~FA","text_ar":"لَتَعُودُونَّ فِيهَا اَسَاوِدَ صُبًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which see in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sb","text_ar":"صب"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the said word being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuE~alFA","text_ar":"فُعَّلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sub~aA^F","text_ar":"صُبَّاً"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being suppressed: (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sb","text_ar":"صب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaA^ahumo","text_ar":"اَصْبَاَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he came upon them suddenly, not having knowledge of their place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a Ealayohimu AlEaduw~a","text_ar":"صَبَاَ عَلَيْهِمُ العَدُوَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, * K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabo'N","text_ar":"صَبْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaEa","text_ar":"صَبَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He guided to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) mentioned by IAar, from AZ. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qud~ima","text_ar":"قُدِّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi TaEaAmN famaA SabaA^a walaA A^aSobaA^a","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ طَعَامٌ فَمَا صَبَاَ وَلَا اَصْبَاَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Food was presented to him, and he did not put"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his finger"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobaEahu","text_ar":"اـِصْبَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaEa","text_ar":"صَبَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) mentioned by IAar. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^a fiY AlT~aEaAmi","text_ar":"صَبَاَ فِى الطَّعَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a camel]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put his head into the food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabaga","text_ar":"صَبَغَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sbg","text_ar":"صبغ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA^ato fiyhaA raA^osahaA","text_ar":"صَبَاَتْ فِيهَا رَاْسَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She put her head into it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabagato","text_ar":"صَبَغَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in that art.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","AO","TA","Msb","T"]},{"entry_id":"n23737","headword_ar":"صَبَا","root":"Sbw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaSobuw","text_ar":"يَصْبُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabowapN","text_ar":"صَبْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabowN","text_ar":"صَبْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuw~N","text_ar":"صُبُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFY","text_ar":"صِبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the CK (erroneously)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabFY","text_ar":"صَبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) [app., in its primary acceptation,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was a youth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"child;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with an explanation of a phrase in what follows, and with explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which will be found below: ―         -b2-  and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, youthfully ignorant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [and, as seems to be indicated in the TA,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he indulged in amorous dalliance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a sense in which the verb, more especially with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v. infrà) for its inf. n., is very frequently used:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he inclined to ignorant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silly, and youthful, conduct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tSAbY","text_ar":"تصابى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ibaA","text_ar":"الصِّبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awoq","text_ar":"الشَّوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. “ desire ”]: (S: [see an ex. of the inf. n. of the latter verb in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAba","text_ar":"شَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$yb","text_ar":"شيب"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as inf. ns., signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining the heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"to any one; and have other significations expl. in what follows: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSaAbK","text_ar":"تَصَابٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manifesting passionate love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) [but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are often used in different senses: thus Et-Tebreezee says that] in the following hemistich of a poem by Dureyd Ibn-Es-Simmeh,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"SabaA maA SabaA Hat~aY EalaA Al$~ayobu raA^osahu"},{"kind":"text","text":"the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SbA","text_ar":"صبا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ibaY","text_ar":"الصِّبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ibaA","text_ar":"الصِّبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and the second"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SbA","text_ar":"صبا"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abaA='u","text_ar":"الصَّبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfataA='u","text_ar":"الفَتَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so that the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He engaged in play,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sport, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ibaY","text_ar":"الصِّبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amorous dalliance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as he was a youth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until hoariness came upon his head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he engaged in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ibiY","text_ar":"الصِّبِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as he engaged therein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Ham p. 380.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiYa","text_ar":"صَبِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaSobaY","text_ar":"يَصْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [or both, as will appear from what follows,] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He played,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sported, with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyaAn","text_ar":"صِبْيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted in the manner of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyaAn","text_ar":"صِبْيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K: *) or both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as inf. ns., signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting as a youth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"child;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"playing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sporting, with youths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tSb~Y","text_ar":"تصبّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tSAbY","text_ar":"تصابى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of an old man, signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted in a youthful, boyish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"childish, manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA","text_ar":"صَبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuw~N","text_ar":"صُبُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabowapN","text_ar":"صَبْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inclined."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA A_ilayohaA","text_ar":"صَبَا اـِلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inclined to her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a woman; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiYa","text_ar":"صَبِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabato A_ilayohi","text_ar":"صَبَتْ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabiyato","text_ar":"صَبِيَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She inclined to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sub~N","text_ar":"صُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sb","text_ar":"صب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA A_ilayohi","text_ar":"صَبَا اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohaA","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabowapN","text_ar":"صَبْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SubowapN","text_ar":"صُبْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuw~N","text_ar":"صُبُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiYa","text_ar":"صَبِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He yearned towards, longed for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabati Aln~axolapu","text_ar":"صَبَتِ النَّخْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSobuw","text_ar":"تَصْبُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm-tree inclined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaned, towards the male palm-tree that was distant from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabati Alr~aAEiyapu","text_ar":"صَبَتِ الرَّاعِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSobuw","text_ar":"تَصْبُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuw~N","text_ar":"صُبُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pasturing beast inclined its head and put it upon the pasturage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [See also 2.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabato","text_ar":"صَبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSobuw","text_ar":"تَصْبُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subuw~N","text_ar":"صُبُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabFA","text_ar":"صَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) in [some of] the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA'","text_ar":"صَبَاء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) said of the wind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abaA","text_ar":"الصَّبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It blew."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SubiYa Alqawomu","text_ar":"صُبِىَ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, were blown upon by the wind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abaA","text_ar":"الصَّبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","KL","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n23742","headword_ar":"صَبًا","root":"Sbw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is of the fem. gender, and] is a subst. and an epithet, [so that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN SabFA","text_ar":"رِيحٌ صَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabFA","text_ar":"صَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHu AlS~abaA","text_ar":"رِيحُ الصَّبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M, TA,) [and signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"east wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an easterly wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that blows from the place of sunrise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind of which the mean place whence it blows is the place where the sun rises when the night and day are equal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the opposite wind of which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabuwr","text_ar":"دَبُور"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind that faces the House"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Kaabeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that blows from the point opposite to the corner, of the Kaabeh, that is between the Black Stone and the door"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though yearning towards the House: (M, TA:) or, accord. to IAar, (M,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind of which the place whence it blows extends from the place of rising of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uray~aA","text_ar":"الثُّرَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Pleiades"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAt naEo$","text_ar":"بَنَات نَعْش"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tail of Ursa Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) [it is often commended by poets as a gentle and pleasant gale, like the Zephyr with us:] the dual is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabawaAni","text_ar":"صَبَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabayaAni","text_ar":"صَبَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, M, K:) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabawaAtN","text_ar":"صَبَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaA='N","text_ar":"اَصْبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","Msb","S","K","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n23743","headword_ar":"صِبًا","root":"Sbw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[also written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFY","text_ar":"صِبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the former with kesr and the short alif, and the latter with fet-h and the long alif, (S, Msb,) [both mentioned before as inf. ns.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Youth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boyhood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiY~","text_ar":"صَبِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"childhood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`lika fiY SibaAhu","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلِكَ فِى صِبَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaAy^ihi","text_ar":"صَبَايِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in his youth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boyhood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his childhood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) [See also an ex. in a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$fE","text_ar":"شفع"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  And the former [or each, as is shown in the first sentence of this art.,] has also a signification derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awoqu","text_ar":"الشَّوْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or “ desire; ” i. e., each signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An inclining to ignorant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silly, and youthful, conduct; and amorous dalliance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabowapN","text_ar":"صَبْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [the same, as is also shown in the first sentence of this art., or, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibFA","text_ar":"صِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaA='N","text_ar":"صَبَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignorance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolishness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silliness, of youth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and amorous dalliance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA.) [See an ex. of the first in a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AdY","text_ar":"ادى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and another in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAraDa","text_ar":"عَارَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb"]}]}}